                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16576476" author="jasobrown" created="Fri, 10 Aug 2018 15:55:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.11/conf/jvm.options#L197&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;previous, 3.11 settings&lt;/a&gt; as a guide, reverting the java8 settings was simple. However, java11 was not as trivial. A naive reenabling of java8&apos;s GC settings yielded:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Unrecognized VM option &apos;UseParNewGC&apos;                                                                                                                                                                               
Error: Could not create the Java Virtual Machine.
Error: A fatal exception has occurred. Program will exit.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;UseParNewGC&lt;/tt&gt; was deprecated in java 9 and &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8151084&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;removed in java 10&lt;/a&gt;. Once that flag is removed, cassandra can start and run properly. However, this is this log statement upon process start:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM warning: Option UseConcMarkSweepGC was deprecated in version 9.0 and will likely be removed in a future release.                                                                          
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For those who haven&apos;t been playing along with every gyration of the JDK, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8142518&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CMS collector is deprecated&lt;/a&gt;. However, CMS &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8163329&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;might not be removed&lt;/a&gt;, but might not be supported directly by the OpenJDK project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either way, it appears that simply removing &lt;tt&gt;UseParNewGC&lt;/tt&gt; form the java 11 config gets us back to on-par with the java 8 config.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch available here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;14636&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jasobrown/cassandra/tree/14636&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://circleci.com/gh/jasobrown/workflows/cassandra/tree/14636&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;utests &amp;amp; dtests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Failed dtests are known issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16576589" author="jrwest" created="Fri, 10 Aug 2018 17:10:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My understanding is &lt;tt&gt;UseParNewGC&lt;/tt&gt; is implicit in Java 10+. Otherwise it might be worth adding a note about that specific change. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
